* Desmonus finally reached the small clearing from where that deliciouse 
smell was coming from, and now the scent of it simply made her stomach growl 
and her mouth water.
Finally, she would be able to feast.
However, it was still daylight and she was basically blind. But she could 
see with her senses good enough for what she needed.
It was down there, she could smell it. Her meal.
Desmonus could sense another food sorce right beside it, but it didn't smell 
quite as tasty as the other one.
She decended quietly into the forest around the clearing, folding her wings 
in beside her once her feet touched the ground.
With quietness she crept towards her intended prey. Keeping to the shadows 
to make sure that she couldn't be seen.*
